modules.description: Provides functions to render nested data structures such as boxes, lists, arrays, and tables in text and HTML formats. Operates on custom data types representing structured content with hierarchical elements. Used to generate formatted output for debugging, documentation, or user interfaces.

Registers custom text extensions with styling support, computes string display width for monospace rendering, and converts box structures to styled terminal output. Operates on string data and box structures representing formatted text layouts. Outputs boxes to terminals, files, or formatters with customizable indentation and styling.
